# Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Snitch frontend project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` v2.0.1 via npm
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the resolved dependency tree

### 2. Analytics Configuration
**Modified: `frontend/src/App.jsx`**
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';`
- Added `<Analytics />` component to the main App component's JSX structure
- Component placed alongside the Toaster component at the root level

## Implementation Details

The installation followed the latest official Vercel Analytics documentation from:
https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart

For this Vite + React project:
1. The Analytics component was imported from `@vercel/analytics/react`
2. The component was added to the root App.jsx file to track analytics across all routes
3. The component requires no additional configuration and will automatically start tracking when deployed to Vercel

## Framework Context
- **Framework**: Vite 6.4.3 with React 18.3.1
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Entry Point**: frontend/src/main.jsx
- **App Component**: frontend/src/App.jsx

## Verification
- Build completed successfully with `npm run build`
- No errors or warnings introduced
- All existing functionality preserved
- Build artifacts are optimized and compressed

## Next Steps
To enable analytics tracking:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics section
3. Verify tracking in the browser's Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`
4. Analytics data will be available in the Vercel dashboard after deployment

Note: Analytics will only function when deployed to Vercel. Local development will not generate tracked data.
